entries.s_12: Good. Let me know if I can be of further assistance.
entries.s_20: I'm speechless. I would never in a million, billion years have suspected the Lt. Col. capable of something like this. It would appear that working for him was much less of an honor than I once thought.
entries.s_32: Any luck finding the medal yet?
entries.s_34: You're here about Lt. Col. Quelsh's missing medal?
entries.s_36: Yes, that's right. Can you tell me what happened?
entries.s_38: I wish I knew. He wears it practically every day. I can't imagine when someone could have stolen it. But I must admit that I've searched everywhere I could think of, and yet I've found no sign of it. Now that I think about it, there is one thing that might mean something.
entries.s_43: Working for Lt. Col. Quelsh is an honor that I would be hesitant to relinquish.
entries.s_45: I noticed some thugs hanging around the area recently. I think they call themselves Braggan's Fist. Whatever that means. They are often loitering around in the slums area. You might want to see if they were involved.
